Aggregate.shortDescription: Performs grouped or ungrouped aggregation on output of its child.

Append.shortDescription: Combines the results of its children.

Bitmap Heap Scan.shortDescription: Reads a Bitmap of physical row locations and fetches the data referenced in it.

Bitmap Index Scan.shortDescription: Scans through the index and produces a bitmap of physical row locations to be processed by other Bitmap nodes.

BitmapAnd.shortDescription: Calculates the intersection of two physical row location bitmaps.

BitmapOr.shortDescription: Calculates the union of two physical row location bitmaps.

CTE Scan.shortDescription: Scans the result of a common table expression (WITH clause).

Custom Scan.shortDescription: Scans the database object using a custom scan implementation from an external module.

Foreign Scan.shortDescription: Scans the foreign table (a table-like database object referencing data stored outside of Postgres).

Function Scan.shortDescription: Scans the result of a set-returning function (like unnest or regexp_split_to_table).

Gather.shortDescription: Combines the results from several children producing data in parallel.

Gather Merge.shortDescription: Combines the results from several children producing sorted data in parallel, in the specified order.

Group.shortDescription: Processes sorted input and groups it by the specified field.

Hash.shortDescription: Reads data into a hash table, where it can be looked up by the hash key.

Hash Join.shortDescription: Scans through the outer table, looking for matches in a hash table built from the inner table data and keyed by join key.

Incremental Sort.shortDescription: Takes partially sorted data from a child node and produces output sorted according to a more specific sort key, using either memory if available (depending on the work_mem setting) or “spilling” to disk. This can be used if the input can be scanned in a partially-sorted manner—e.g., if scanning a btree index compatible with the desired sort order.

Index Only Scan.shortDescription: Scans through the index to fetch a single value or a range of values in index order without reading table data.

Index Scan.shortDescription: Scans through the index to fetch a single value or a range of values in index order from the table.

Limit.shortDescription: Sorts the output of a child node.

Lock Rows.shortDescription: Executes the locking behavior of a FOR UPDATE clause.

Materialize.shortDescription: Materialize the result of its child node in memory (to avoid re-computing the values).

Merge Append.shortDescription: Combines the results of its sorted children, in the specified order.

Merge Join.shortDescription: Joins two children already sorted by their shared join key.

ModifyTable.shortDescription: Modifies a table according to the rows referenced by its child.

Nested Loop.shortDescription: Loops through rows in the outer table, and for each, loops through rows in the inner table looking for matches.

Project Set.shortDescription: Apply a projection that includes set-returning functions to the output tuples of the outer plan.

Recursive Union.shortDescription: Evaluates a recursive common table expression (WITH RECURSIVE clause).

Result.shortDescription: Evaluates an expression that does not depend on table data.

Seq Scan.shortDescription: Scans through the entire table row-by-row in an arbitrary order.

SetOp.shortDescription: Combines data from children for set operations like UNION, INTERSECT, and EXCEPT.

Sort.shortDescription: Takes data from a child node and produces sorted output, using either memory if available (depending on the work_mem setting) or “spilling” to disk. This is obviously necessary if the output needs to be sorted, though sometimes the input can be scanned in an already-sorted manner instead—e.g., if scanning a btree index compatible with the desired sort order.

Subquery Scan.shortDescription: Scans the output of a subquery.

Table Sample Scan.shortDescription: Scans the table using the TABLESAMPLE sampling mechanism.

Tid Scan.shortDescription: Scan through a table using internal row identifiers.

Unique.shortDescription: Processes sorted input and eliminates adjacent duplicates.

Values Scan.shortDescription: Scans the literal VALUES clause (an inline table).

Window Aggregate.shortDescription: Implements aggregation in window functions (OVER clause).

Work Table Scan.shortDescription: Scans the work table used in evaluating a recursive common table expression (WITH clause).
